00:45:44.970 --> 00:45:46.247
What else would I say?

00:45:46.247 --> 00:45:47.810
Know your neighborhood.

00:45:47.810 --> 00:45:48.760
Know your customer.

00:45:48.760 --> 00:45:50.610
Know what you want.

00:45:50.610 --> 00:45:52.780
And then be willing to make the
adjustments once you get

00:45:52.780 --> 00:45:55.430
open, to let your ego get out of
the way and realize that if

00:45:55.430 --> 00:45:56.840
these folks don't walk
through your front

00:45:56.840 --> 00:45:58.850
door, you're screwed.

00:45:58.850 --> 00:46:00.900
And they might once, but they
have to walk through

00:46:00.900 --> 00:46:03.420
more than one time.

00:46:03.420 --> 00:46:07.780
You have to learn a customer
service that is inviting and

00:46:07.780 --> 00:46:09.470
makes them want to come back.

00:46:09.470 --> 00:46:12.120
And that's the number
one thing.

00:46:12.120 --> 00:46:14.570
So many chefs go in, they want
to open their own place

00:46:14.570 --> 00:46:15.700
because they want to
cook their food.

00:46:15.700 --> 00:46:16.540
Well, screw you.

00:46:16.540 --> 00:46:18.650
Your food is their food.

00:46:18.650 --> 00:46:19.862
That's who you owe to.

00:46:19.862 --> 00:46:22.300
And if they don't come back and
vote for you with their

00:46:22.300 --> 00:46:24.880
dollars, you're done.

00:46:24.880 --> 00:46:27.610
And that's why you see the
restaurant churn so often.

00:46:27.610 --> 00:46:30.120
Because 75% of restaurants go
out of business through

00:46:30.120 --> 00:46:32.180
employee theft.

00:46:32.180 --> 00:46:34.510
And the other 25% go out of
business because the chefs are

00:46:34.510 --> 00:46:37.050
stupid, and they're egomaniacs
and they can't

00:46:37.050 --> 00:46:38.390
get their act together.

00:46:38.390 --> 00:46:41.330
They have their tunnel vision
on what they do rather than

00:46:41.330 --> 00:46:43.720
business as a bigger picture.

00:46:43.720 --> 00:46:45.770
Employee theft, you've probably
all benefited from.

00:46:45.770 --> 00:46:47.450
When's the last time you went to
a restaurant where you knew

00:46:47.450 --> 00:46:49.730
the bartender, he handed you
a drink, didn't charge you?

00:46:49.730 --> 00:46:50.810
That's employee theft.

00:46:50.810 --> 00:46:53.530
I'm sure he didn't go to the
till and pay for it himself.

00:46:53.530 --> 00:46:55.040
It's the most-- it's nice.

00:46:55.040 --> 00:46:57.180
We call it customer
service sometimes.

00:46:57.180 --> 00:46:59.300
But that's just-- that's
employee theft.

00:46:59.300 --> 00:47:00.770
And it happens through
the back door.

00:47:00.770 --> 00:47:02.230
It happens through
the front door.

00:47:02.230 --> 00:47:06.130
And it is something that
you can't really stop.

00:47:06.130 --> 00:47:08.580
You just have to mitigate
the damage from it.

00:47:08.580 --> 00:47:11.540
But that's something to think
about building into your

00:47:11.540 --> 00:47:12.410
pricing structure.

00:47:12.410 --> 00:47:15.170
And in bakeries, it's
all about waste.

00:47:15.170 --> 00:47:18.230
What do you do with those
cookies you didn't sell today?

00:47:18.230 --> 00:47:19.480
There's a lot of--

00:47:19.480 --> 00:47:24.420
you have to-- if you make 20
cookies, you can't think--

00:47:24.420 --> 00:47:27.470
if you made 24 cookies, say, out
of a recipe, and you think

00:47:27.470 --> 00:47:29.850
how to price those cookies, it's
not just the ingredients

00:47:29.850 --> 00:47:33.010
of the cost of the dough, or the
labor it takes you to make

00:47:33.010 --> 00:47:34.030
the 24 cookies.

00:47:34.030 --> 00:47:35.566
It's at the end of the
day, how many did you

00:47:35.566 --> 00:47:36.630
have to throw away?

00:47:36.630 --> 00:47:39.350
So if you had to throw away
six of the 24, you have to

00:47:39.350 --> 00:47:42.610
build the cost of those six back
into your first 18, so

00:47:42.610 --> 00:47:44.370
that you know what you
should properly be

00:47:44.370 --> 00:47:46.450
charging for the cookie.

00:47:46.450 --> 00:47:48.220
Unless you want to have--

00:47:48.220 --> 00:47:50.240
unless you build in that number,
your numbers aren't

00:47:50.240 --> 00:47:52.970
going to work.

00:47:52.970 --> 00:47:53.840
Be thinking about
those things.

